description:
ReSharper annotations are useful to increase accuracy and precision of ReSharper code inspections, reduce false positive warnings, explicitly declare purity and nullability in your code, deal with implicit usages of members, support special semantic of APIs in ASP.NET and XAML frameworks and etc.

      By default all attribute usages are erased from metadata, so no actual binary reference to 'JetBrains.Annotations.dll' assembly will be produced. If you need to preserve annotations in metadata, just define 'JETBRAINS_ANNOTATIONS' conditional compilation symbol in your projects.
releaseNotes:
• This annotations package is now officially maintained by JetBrains.
• By default all attribute usages are erased from metadata, so no actual binary reference to 'JetBrains.Annotations.dll' assembly will be produced.

title: JetBrains ReSharper Annotations
